<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>GitHub Actions Info App</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.2/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
  <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark mb-4">
    <div class="container">
      <a class="navbar-brand" href="#">GitHub Actions Info</a>
    </div>
  </nav>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8 mx-auto">
        <div class="card shadow-sm mb-4">
          <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
            <h3>What are GitHub Actions?</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <p>
              <strong>GitHub Actions</strong> is a powerful CI/CD tool built into GitHub. It lets you automate workflows for building, testing, and deploying your code right from your repository.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-3">
              <li class="list-group-item">Automate software workflows</li>
              <li class="list-group-item">Run tests and builds on every push</li>
              <li class="list-group-item">Deploy applications automatically</li>
              <li class="list-group-item">Integrate with third-party services</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/actions" class="btn btn-success" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-info text-center">
          <strong>Tip:</strong> You can customize your workflows using YAML files in your repository!
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <footer class="bg-dark text-white text-center py-3 mt-4">
    &copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> GitHub Actions Info App
  </footer>
</body>
</html>